Spray a 9x13-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Mix honey graham cereal, peanut butter cereal, and toasted oat cereal together in a bowl. Combine marshmallows and butter in a large pot over low heat; cook and stir until melted and smooth, 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over cereal mixture; stir until mixed. Pour cereal and marshmallow mixture into prepared baking pan. Spray hands with cooking spray; pat mixture down evenly. Let cool, about 10 minutes. Cut into squares.